3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING A MONTANA UNIVERSITY INVESTIGATION
5 COMMITTEE; PROVIDING DUTIES AND MEMBERS; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; PROVIDING FOR
6 CONTINGENT VOIDNESS; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
7
8 WHEREAS, President Donald Trump recently issued an executive order directing federal agencies to
9 freeze spending related to certain grants and loans; and
10 WHEREAS, in response to directions from the White House, the National Institutes of Health (NIH) will
11 implement a 15% cap on overhead costs related to grant-funded research, including costs related to
12 equipment, facilities, and support staff; and
13 WHEREAS, in Montana, the NIH grant funding supports research on opioid addiction, traumatic brain
14 injuries, physical and mental health in indigenous communities, and other important topics to Montanans; and
15 WHEREAS, the 15% cap could shift approximately $5 million in research costs to the state; and
16 WHEREAS, the cap on indirect costs could affect the use of lab space and equipment, graduate
17 students who conduct research as part of their studies, and other staff whose reporting, budgeting, and grant
18 writing work supports research; and
19 WHEREAS, the biggest driver of enrollment growth at the University of Montana has been in the health
20 department; and
21 WHEREAS, at Montana State University, undergraduate and graduate students will be affected by the
22 cap as well as the private companies who contract with the university for research; and
23 WHEREAS, private industries rely on the universities for research that would otherwise be outside the
24 reach of those businesses, including tests in high-end facilities that have been established at the universities.
25
26 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
27
28 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Montana university system investigation committee -- membership -
