1 - meetings. (1) (a) There is a committee to investigate:
2 (i) civil rights violations and acts of censorship committed by the Montana university system. The
3 committee shall gather testimony on the record from Montana students on any civil rights violations or acts of
4 censorship that the students have experienced or witnessed at Montana public universities and colleges and
5 make findings and recommendations for state and federal officials.
6 (ii) the anticipated effects and impacts of recent federal spending freezes on research being
7 conducted on Montana university system campuses, including but not limited to enrollment, budgets, staff and
8 faculty, secondary effects on Montana businesses that rely on the university system, and the resulting impacts
9 on Montana's economy.
10 (b) The committee shall report in physical and electronic copy all findings and recommendations to
11 the president of the United States, the United States department of justice, the United States department of
12 education, the leadership of both houses of the United States congress, all members of the Montana
13 congressional delegation, the governor of Montana, the Montana department of justice, the office of public
14 instruction, the speaker of the Montana house of representatives, and the president of the Montana senate.
15 (2) The committee consists of six legislators appointed as follows:
16 (a) three members of the house of representatives appointed by the speaker of the house. One of
17 the members must be a member of the minority party and be appointed after consultation with the minority
18 leader.
19 (b) three members of the senate appointed by the committee on committees. One of the members
20 must be a member of the minority party.
21 (3) The appointments must be made within 30 days of [the effective date of this act]. A vacancy on
22 the committee must be filled in the same manner as the original appointment.
23 (4) The committee shall elect a presiding officer and a vice presiding officer.
24 (5) A committee member is entitled to salary and expenses as provided in 5-2-302.
25 (6) The committee may not meet more than three times and shall complete its work by September
26 15, 2026.
27 (7) The legislative services division shall provide staff assistance to the committee.
